quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  7,74,"Remember when He made you successors after [the people of] ‘Ad, and settled you in the land: you build palaces in its plains, and hew houses out of the mountains. So remember Allah’s bounties, and do not act wickedly on the earth, causing corruption.’"
  7,75,"The elite of his people who were arrogant said to those who were oppressed—to those among them who had faith—‘Do you know that Salih has been sent by his Lord?’ They said, ‘We indeed believe in what he has been sent with.’"
  7,76,"Those who were arrogant said, ‘We indeed disbelieve in what you have believed.’"
  7,77,"So they hamstrung the She-camel and defied the command of their Lord, and they said, ‘O Salih, bring us what you threaten us with, if you are one of the apostles.’"
  7,78,"Thereupon the earthquake seized them, and they lay lifeless prostrate in their homes"
  7,79,"So he abandoned them [to their fate], and said, ‘O my people! Certainly I communicated to you the message of my Lord, and I was your well-wisher, but you did not like well-wishers.’"
  7,80,"And Lot, when he said to his people, ‘What! Do you commit an outrage none in the world ever committed before you"
  7,81,"Indeed you come to men with desire instead of women! Indeed, you are a profligate lot.’"